item.title: Anya add a quote by Charlotte Brontë
item.description: "I am not an angel,' I asserted; 'and I will not be one till I die: I will be myself. Mr. Rochester, you must neither expect nor exact anything celestial of me - for you will not get it, any more than I shall get it of you: which I do not at all anticipate." -- Charlotte Brontë

item.title: Anya add a quote by George Carlin
item.description: "The planet is fine. The people are fucked." -- George Carlin

item.title: Anya add a quote by Bertrand Russell
item.description: "Our great democracies still tend to think that a stupid man is more likely to be honest than a clever man, and our politicians take advantage of this prejudice by pretending to be even more stupid than nature made them." -- Bertrand Russell
